<!-- HERO -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-eyebrow">Your Result</div>
  <div class="hero-season">A season called <em>Reorientation</em></div>
  <h1 class="hero-archetype">The <em>Seeker</em></h1>
  <div class="hero-rule"></div>
  <p class="hero-lede">You've outgrown the life you've been living and you haven't told a single person.</p>
</section>

<!-- CONTENT -->
<div class="content">

  <!-- SECTION 01 — RECOGNITION -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">One</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">What you already <em>know.</em></h2>

    <p class="body-text">Not to your partner. Not to your closest friend. Not even to yourself in any way you couldn't take back.</p>

    <p class="body-text">Saying it would make it real. Once it's real, you'd have to do something about it. And you don't yet know what.</p>

    <p class="body-text">So you carry it. You handle your days. You show up the way you're supposed to.</p>

    <p class="body-text emphasis">And underneath all of it, a low persistent hum: I can't stay here.</p>

    <p class="body-text">You're standing in the space between the woman you've been and the woman you can feel forming. That gap is wider than anyone in your life knows.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 02 — THE SEASON -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">Two</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">This is the season of <em>Reorientation.</em></h2>

    <p class="body-text">You already know something has shifted. You felt it before this quiz. You felt it before today.</p>

    <p class="body-text">What you don't have yet is language. The words to call this what it is so it stops feeling like restlessness and starts feeling like direction.</p>

    <p class="body-text">People will hand you the easy names for what you're in. Midlife crisis. Stage of life. Hormones. Be grateful. It'll pass.</p>

    <p class="body-text declarative">It won't pass. This is development.</p>

    <p class="body-text">The version of you who built your current life finished her assignment. The next version has already started forming. You can feel her. You just can't see her clearly yet.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 03 — THE WORK -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">Three</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">What this <em>actually</em> asks of you.</h2>

    <p class="body-text">Name what you've outgrown. Specifically. Honestly. Without flinching.</p>

    <p class="body-text emphasis">You cannot choose who you're becoming until you know exactly who you've been.</p>

    <p class="body-text">That's the first move. Everything else comes after.</p>
  </section>

</div>

<!-- CTA — Dynamic based on readiness -->
<section class="cta-section">
  <div class="cta-inner">

    <!-- READY NOW VERSION -->
    <div id="cta-ready-now" style="display:none;">
      <div class="cta-eyebrow">The Next Move</div>
      <h2 class="cta-title">Name Her<em>™</em></h2>

      <p class="cta-body">Thirty days of identity work for the woman who already knows she's been performing.</p>

      <p class="cta-body">You'll spend thirty days seeing the version of you who built this life. Why she built it. Who she built it for. What she's been protecting. What she's been costing you.</p>

      <p class="cta-body">Daily audio that says the things you've been thinking in private. Worksheets that put language to the woman you've been performing as. A small private group of women who are in this season with you.</p>

      <p class="cta-body center">You will not leave with a new identity. You will leave with the language for the one you've been living as. Which is the only honest place to start choosing from.</p>

      <div class="cta-divider"></div>

      <p class="cta-body" style="text-align:center; margin-bottom: 8px;">The first cohort opens September 1.</p>

      <a href="https://nextseasonher.com/name-her-waitlist" class="cta-button">Join the Waitlist</a>

      <p class="cta-footnote">Founding cohort. 15 to 25 women. $197.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- READY LATER VERSION -->
    <div id="cta-ready-later" style="display:none;">
      <div class="cta-eyebrow">Before You Go Any Further</div>
      <h2 class="cta-title">Listen to <em>this.</em></h2>

      <p class="cta-body">A short audio I recorded for women who recognize themselves in The Seeker but aren't yet ready to move.</p>

      <p class="cta-body">Twenty minutes. Worth headphones.</p>

      <p class="cta-body">It names what's underneath the hesitation. And it tells you what to do with this season while you're still deciding what comes next.</p>

      <div class="cta-divider"></div>

      <a href="https://nextseasonher.com/welcome-audio" class="cta-button">Listen Now</a>

